)attr default(%+`)
  ` type( input) intens(low ) just(left ) hilite(uscore)
  ~ type(text) intens(high) caps(off) just(asis ) hilite(reverse) color(turq)
  [ type(output) intens(high) caps(off) just(left) pas(on)
)Body Expand(}})
%Tutorial -}-}~The z ISPF Git Interface (zigi)%}-}- Tutorial
%Selection ===>`ZCMD                                                          +
+
                              %Logging Activity+
+
%zigi+provides the ability to log all, or nearly all, processing. This
+is accomplished by writing to a file created in the users OMVS Home
+directory. The file has a date and time stamp of when it is initially
+created. The format is:%zigidebug.dyyddd.thhmmss+
+
+To initiate logging do:
   +1) Allocate a DUMMY DD to ZIGIDEBG
+
+or 2) Issue the%DEBUG+command from within zigi to be prompted:
+
+     %DEbug ON+   To enable logging
+     %DEbug OFf+  To disable logging
+     %DEbug View+ To ISPF View the active log file
+
+The log file(s) will also be displayed, if%debug+is used, upon exit from zigi.
+
          +Press the%Enter+key to continue your ZIGI tutorial journey.
)Init
 .cursor = &zcmd
)PROC
 &zcont = zigih100
)END
